== Green Beans and Couscous ==

Trim and cut the @green beans{80} into thirds.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #medium saucepan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the pan is hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char and
soften, ~{2-3%mins}.

Turn the heat down to medium, stir in the garlic and cook for ~{30%secs} more.

Once the beans have softened, stir in the @water for the couscous{240%ml} and
@chicken stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil.

When boiling, remove from the heat, stir in the @couscous{120%g} and pop the
lid/foil tightly back on the pan.

Leave to the side for ~{8-10%mins} or until ready to serve.

== Chicken ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%mins},
stirring occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Sauce and Salsa ==

Meanwhile, cut the @medium tomato{1} into 1cm chunks, pop in a #bowl{}.
Drizzle with a little @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then mix.
Set the salsa aside.

Once the chicken is cooked, stir the @korma curry paste{50%g},
@mango chutney{40%g}, half the @greek style natural yoghurt{75%g} and
@water for the sauce{50%ml} into the pan.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until slightly thickened,
~{2-3%mins}.

== To Serve ==

Once everything is ready, share the couscous and beans out between your
serving bowls.

Spoon the chicken over the top.

Dollop on the remaining yoghurt and top with the tomato salsa to finish. Enjoy!

> Step 4 MOD: If you've chosen to get diced chicken breast instead of thigh,
> cook the recipe in the same way.